# Next.js & React Rules

You are a senior full-stack engineer. Follow these rules for every file.

## Component Naming
`[name].[type].tsx` — types: `ui` `custom` `providers` `layouts` `forms`

## UI Primitives (`components/ui`)
- Use only primitives from `@/components/ui/*.ui` for buttons, inputs, textareas, selects, checkboxes, switches, labels, dialogs, etc.
- Import examples: `button.ui`, `input.ui`, `input-group.ui`, `field.ui`, `select.ui`, `textarea.ui`
- Never use raw `<button>`, `<input>`, `<textarea>`, or `<select>` in features, app routes, or `*.custom.tsx` — compose from UI primitives instead
- Extend styling via `variant` / `size` / `className` on primitives, not duplicate markup
- `button.tsx` / `input.tsx` (shadcn CLI stubs) are internal only — application code uses `*.ui.tsx`

## Variants — no inline conditionals
```tsx
const Variants = {
  size: { sm: "px-3 py-1.5 text-sm", md: "px-4 py-2", lg: "px-6 py-3" },
  intent: { primary: "bg-primary text-white", ghost: "hover:bg-accent" },
} as const
type Size = keyof typeof Variants.size
type Intent = keyof typeof Variants.intent
```

## TypeScript
- `strict: true`, no `any` (use `unknown`)
- Discriminated unions for state; `as const` for literals

## Server Actions
- [ ] `'use server'`
- [ ] Auth check (`getServerSession`)
- [ ] Zod input validation
- [ ] Typed error return (no naked throws)
- [ ] `revalidatePath` / `revalidateTag` after mutation

## API Routes
- [ ] Named HTTP method export
- [ ] Auth check → `401`
- [ ] Zod validation → `400`
- [ ] `{ data, error }` response shape
- [ ] Rate limit → `429`

## React
- Rules of Hooks — no hooks in loops or conditions
- `React.memo` + `useCallback` / `useMemo` to stabilize props
- `React.lazy` + `Suspense` for code splitting
- Error Boundaries around critical sections
- Custom hooks: `use` prefix, typed return

## State
- Server Components for server state
- React Query for async client state
- Zustand for UI-only state (small stores)
- `nuqs` for shareable URL state

## Prisma
- Singleton client, server-side only
- `select` only needed fields
- Zod before mutations; `$transaction` for atomic ops

## Performance
- Measure first — never guess
- Fix N+1s, add indexes, paginate lists
- `next/image` with dimensions + WebP

## Security
- Never trust client data
- Validate auth in every Action and Route
- `httpOnly` cookies, never expose internal errors